    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "Introducing Moonlake, AI for creating world simulations.\n\n\nFINANCE \u0026 STRATEGIC OPERATIONS LEAD\n\nLocation: San Mateo, CA\nType: Full-time · On-site\n\n\nOVERVIEW\n\nMoonlake is building the next generation of AI infrastructure for interactive digital worlds. Our mission is to enable anyone to create, simulate, and interact with rich environments using natural language and multimodal inputs, turning simple ideas into worlds with structure, logic, and agents that can perceive and act.\n\nOur team has raised $28M in seed funding from NVIDIA Ventures, Threshold Ventures, AIX ventures and notable angels including Naval Ravikant and Jeff Dean to build the foundational layer for the future of AI - powering everything from creative tools and games to robotics training, simulations, and digital twins. Our goal is to make building and experimenting with these environments as accessible and scalable as publishing video on the internet.\n\nMoonlake AI is looking for a Finance \u0026 Strategic Operations hire to help build the financial infrastructure of a rapidly growing frontier AI company.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of finance, strategy, and operations.\n\nYou will work closely with leadership on financial planning, fundraising preparation, and strategic decision-making.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n\nFINANCIAL PLANNING\n\n - Build and maintain financial models\n\n - Support budgeting and forecasting\n\n\nSTRATEGIC ANALYSIS\n\n - Support pricing strategy and monetization models\n\n - Analyze product economics and growth metrics\n\n\nFUNDRAISING PREPARATION\n\n - Support investor reporting and financial materials\n\n - Assist leadership in preparing fundraising narratives\n\n\nFINANCIAL OPERATIONS\n\n - Maintain financial systems and processes\n\n - Work with external accounting partners\n\n - Ensure operational financial hygiene\n\n\nWHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - Background in finance, consulting, or strategy\n\n - Strong analytical and modeling skills\n\n - Ability to operate in ambiguous environments\n\n - Interest in startups and frontier technology\n\nNice to have:\n\n - Experience in startups\n\n - Experience in venture-backed companies\n\n - MBA or equivalent experience\n\nWe are committed to being an on-site, in-person team currently based in San Mateo",
